The National Cyber Workforce and Education Summit will be held on July 19, 2022, at the White House. It will be attended by National Cyber Director Chris Inglis, Secretary of Commerce Gina M. Raimondo, Secretary of Labor Martin J. Walsh, Secretary of Homeland Security Alejandro N. Mayorkas, and other senior representatives from the Federal Government, private sector executives, and thought leaders from the cyber community and academia. The summit aims to address the national security challenge posed by the approximately 700,000 open cybersecurity positions in America. Participants will discuss ways to improve cybersecurity through awareness, education, and training, and to ensure that all Americans can benefit from the digital domain. Further information on participants and announcements will be provided.